The similar option of a minimum period of validity, during which the ruling may not be rescinded by the
Revenue, is generally endorsed in the responses. See, for example, Simons Tax Intelligence 1996 at p. 685;
CIT, Pre-Transaction Rulings (CIR/7/96), SS 3.9-3.11; ICAEW, Tax 7/96: Pre-Transaction Rulings, para. 28.
